Zephany Nurse has finally been allowed to reveal the name given to her by her kidnapper. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Zephany Nurse has revealed her real identity as Miche Solomons. Solomons has finally been allowed to reveal the name given to her by her kidnapper. It comes in the wake of the release of the 22-year-old's autobiography. The young woman was kidnapped from Cape Town's Groote Schuur Hospital as a newborn. READ: How to protect yourself from online identity theft She was reunited with her biological parents when she was 17. Solomons applied to the North Gauteng High Court for the scrapping of an interim interdict protecting her identity. Her affidavit says she believes the interdict was necessary when she was younger. The woman she had known as her mother was arrested in 2015 and charged with kidnapping and was sentenced to 10-years in prison.